Transocean Seeks to Sell Oil Exploration Arm, Sunday Times Says

-- B y   K a r e n   E e u w e n s
-- 
2011-08-21T09:03:11Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-21/transocean-seeks-to-sell-oil-exploration-arm-sunday-times-says.html
Transocean Ltd. (RIGN) , owner of the oil
rig contracted to BP Plc that blew up in the Gulf of Mexico last
year, hired Bank of America Merrill Lynch to sell its oil
exploration arm, the  Sunday Times  reported, without saying where
it got the information.  The company hopes to get 60 million pounds ($99 million)
for the division known as Challenger Minerals, the newspaper
said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Karen Eeuwens in London at 
 keeuwens@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
